title: CAFEC TH-Series Specialty Filter Paper
description: Experience the superior caliber of CAFEC specialty filter paper, carefully crafted to elevate your coffee brewing experience. Each filter paper is designed to ensure the highest level of quality in every cup. TH-1 This filter paper is 0.15mm thick with one-side crepe (no crepe on inside, crepe on outside). The high paper density filters out coffee fines efficiently - resulting in a clean cup; while the absence of the crepe on the inner surface increases area for fines attachment - causing a build up of water in the brew bed which in turn enhances aroma. TH-2 This filter paper is 0.22mm thick with two-side crepe (low-height). The medium paper density creates an initial smooth flow rate while the two-side crepe gradually restricts flow rate due to the increased surface area for fines attachment. This results in a cup with enhanced body and sweetness. TH-3 This filter paper is 0.28mm thick with two-side crepe (tall-height). The low paper density and tall crepes on both sides of the paper

title: Aquacode
description: Why we love Aquacode? AQUACODE Coffee Brewing Water is a natural product developed to enhance the extraction of specialty coffee. It is different from other chemical synthetic products in the market, AQUACODE is 100% pure natural and made of deep-sea ionic minerals. These are extracted from the deep sea below 700 meters in the Pacific Ocean by low-temperature vacuum concentration. The whole process is additive-free to ensure its naturalness. Water Composition: AQUACODE accurately grasps the magnesium-calcium ion concentration ratio through patented ion tempering technology. Aquacode research team found that a ratio of calcium and magnesium of 1:2.7 creates an ideal balance of acidity and sweetness which can significantly improve the extraction of flavor substances in coffee and perfectly enhance the flavor. You can also adjust the water using the dilution chart to suit your style of brew. Guide on how to use Aquacode:
